	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 11th 8:32 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First of all, I have never been kicked out of a group for it but, I have had some people ask me to lighten up on the PPing because I was leaving very little money.&nbsp;&nbsp;That being said, I have been submitting several messages to the developers attempting to get the real story on PPing and where the coin and loot comes from.  Unfortunately, Abashi on the deveopers board does not seem to want to post or answer my inquiries.<br><br>I read many conflicting view points on where the coin and loot come from.  Some say, it comes from a separate loot and coin store and other feel certain that it comes from the same loot and coin store that everyone draws upon when the mob is killed.  In my own experimenting and research, this is what I feel confident in saying.<br><br>When you PP coin, it is for sure coming from the same place that everyone gets coin from when looting.  I know this from doing two things.  First, I have found in research that it is impossible to PP all of the coin from the mob and at the very least, if you pick it dry, it will still have upon it death one of each type of coin it was carrying.  Here is an example:  If it started with 4pp, 10gp, 8sp, and 12cp, and you pick and pick till you cant pick anymore, it will be left with 1pp, 1gp, 1sp, and 1cp.  When you use the PP skill, depending upon how good your skill level is, will determine what coin you are stealing (and you can only steal one type of coin per attempt).  The other thing is that if you are successful, you will steal exactly half of that amount of coin.  In the example above, if you a successful picking 5gp, then that means you took half the gp the mob had.  Next time you successfully steal gp from the mob it will be half of what is remaining (like 2 or 3gp)This is very easy to test and verify.  Next time you Pick and get some 2 pp, stop picking and loot the mob when it dies.  I guarantee you, you will loot 2pp because you stole half his pp which was a total of 4pp so you will see 2pp remaining.  Also if you did pick 2pp and then you pick again and happen to get pp, I guarantee you that you will only get 1pp the second time because you can only get half of what is remaining on it. Next stop picking and let the mob die and then loot it.  Sure enough, it will only have 1pp left on him.  This confirms to me that I am stealing from the rest of the group (which I don't have any problem doing because I am a rogue).<br><br>Regarding stealing items, this is much harder to determine.  I have read some peoples stories about picking a bronze sword from a mob and then when it dies, there is another bronze sword on him.  I have not witness this for myself so I really cant comment on the items stolen question.<br><br>Lastly, with all of that being said, let me advise you that part of being a successful rogue is not being caught.  A greedy rogue will get caught because some one in the group will catch on if they go to loot and the mob only had one coin of each type every time they loot.  I will never pick a mob dry! If I get one or two pp from stealing, then that tells me that there is at least one more pp on the mob.  So I know that If I am going to loot a mob while grouping, I will cherry pick the mobs I loot by only looting the ones I know have some pp left on them.  I might get it down to 1pp and then maybe get 5 gp next but for sure I stop there so as to not raise suspition (sp?)among the rest of the group.  When I group, and we are going by honor loot, I will loot once every 8-10 mobs, I only do the ones, I know have some pp left on them.  That does not mean the rest of the group won't get pp because at level 35, my PPing skill is at 170 and sometimes I only get copper or silver, and the mob could still have 4 pp on him that I did not know, and the rest of the group still gets some pp.  If I am in a group where we auto split then of course I cant really cherry pick the mobs to loot after the melee because it get split up anyway.<br><br>In my 30's so far, I can easily make 150pp in a full days work in the OverThere between looting and PPing coin and items and there is still plenty of coin the rest of group is getting.<br><br>One final note about ethical issues some of you may have.  If you are a rogue and think that stealing is wrong, then that is fine and you don't have to do it.  However, I am only playing my character the way Verant has designed him to operate.  Rogues are very group dependant if you don't want lots of downtime to heal from barely beating a blue or high green mob.  After level mid 20's, the mobs get too tough to solo.  You could really be smart about things with your equipement and poisons and style of play and maybe solo up to mid 30's but I guarantee you, you will be still running from many mobs and zoning alot and having lots of downtime.  Since we are so group dependant, PPing is really only effective in group play.  Also what is the point in using your PP skill when soloing because you are going to get the same coin and probably the same loot that you would get upon killing the mob.  Verant has designed the class this way on purpose and therefore, I don't have a hard time from stealing while grouping.  The trick is to be smart about using the skill and not be too greedy.  Greedy thieves all ways end up as dead thieves in every fantasy book I have read.<br><br>Enjoy!!!<br>&nbsp;<br>Be Safe in the Shadows:-)<br><br>~Ivan~<br></td></tr>
